.TH manta-cli-delete 1  "delete " 
.SH NAME
manta\-cli\-delete \- Delete system resources
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBmanta\-cli delete\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fIsubcommands\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Delete system resources
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
manta\-cli\-delete\-group(1)
Delete a node group
.TP
manta\-cli\-delete\-node(1)
Remove a node from the system
.TP
manta\-cli\-delete\-kernel\-parameters(1)
Remove kernel parameters from nodes
.TP
manta\-cli\-delete\-boot\-parameters(1)
Delete boot parameters for nodes
.TP
manta\-cli\-delete\-configurations(1)
Delete configurations and all associated data
.TP
manta\-cli\-delete\-session(1)
Delete a configuration session
.TP
manta\-cli\-delete\-images(1)
[experimental] Delete images
.TP
manta\-cli\-delete\-hardware(1)
[experimental] Remove hardware components from a cluster
.TP
manta\-cli\-delete\-redfish\-endpoint(1)
Delete a Redfish endpoint
